(1,'Mercedes-Benz','E55','5.4L','Rear-wheel',2,'69,300',1,'Manual','Clean','WDBUF76J05A714929','Hatchback','Brilliant','Denver,','Black/Blue','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(12, 17, 31); font-family: Poppins;\">The W211 E55 is a fantastic sport sedan that boasts big power from a supercharged V8 engine – the M113 V8, which is known to be more reliable than most other AMG powertrains. This particular E55 boasts reasonably low mileage, a desirable two-tone interior, and some great options, including Drive-Dynamic front seats and Distronic adaptive cruise control. And while this was a Lemon Law buyback car more than 15 years ago, it\'s done many miles since – and it\'s offered with an accident-free Carfax report and no reserve, to enhance the appeal.</span><br></p>','<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.8; font-family: Poppins; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);\"><b>THIS... is a 2004 Mazdaspeed MX-5 Miata, finished in Titanium Gray Metallic with a black and red cloth interior.</b></p><ul><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); position: relative;\">The attached Carfax history report lists no accidents in this Miata\'s past.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); position: relative;\">Factory equipment on this Miata includes a limited-slip differential, Mazdaspeed body kit, silver-painted factory hard top, manual cloth soft top, a Bose sound system, air conditioning, and more listed below.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); position: relative;\">Modifications reported by the seller include 16-inch Konig wheels, a Flyin\' Miata intake and downpipe, a manual boost controller, an HKS recirculating valve, a turbo timer and digital boost gauge, and a Sony 6.2-inch head unit.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); position: relative;\">Referred to as NB internally, the second-generation Miata had an updated design, more power from its inline-4 engine, and a larger trunk, as well as an upgraded interior. For 2004, the Mazdaspeed-tuned model arrived with turbo power and Bilstein suspension enhancements.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); position: relative;\">Power comes from a turbocharged 1.8-liter 4-cylinder, rated at 178 horsepower and 166 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 6-speed manual gearbox and a limited-slip differential.</li></ul>','<ul><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6); position: relative;\">Limited-slip differential</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; marg